    "abstractNote": "The question of the precise distinction between, nafs and r\u016bh, 'soul' and 'spirit' respectively, occupied Arabic-writing thinkers of all faiths. We publish here a short disquisition upon the subject by Ab\u016b al-Faraj ibn al-Tayyib (d. 1048), a Christian philosopher, physician, and theologian of Baghdad, and one of the key figures in the transmission of both the Aristotelian and Galenic traditions. The essay of Ab\u016b al-Faraj is concerned almost exclusively with r\u016bh, specifically the different types of psychic pneuma, each inhabiting one of the three ventricles of the brain, and each responsible for a specific psychic function.",
